******
[2] Tibet
Date: 7 Apr 2017
Source: FIC (Flu Information Centre/Flu in China) Eurosurveillance report [edited]
http://www.flu.org.cn/en/news-19236.html


Tibet confirmed a human H7N9 AIV case in Lhasa city on 3 Apr 2017.

The 41-year-old male patient is a resident of Sichuan province. He came to Tibet in February 2017 and worked in the live poultry trade business.

The patient remained in a designated infectious diseases hospital (The 3rd People's Hospital) for treatment and quarantine.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

******
[3] Sichuan
Date: 9 Apr 2017
Source: FIC (Flu Information Centre/Flu in China) Eurosurveillance report [edited]
http://www.flu.org.cn/en/news-19239.html


A human H7N9 AIV case was reported in Anyuan county of Ziyang city of Sichuan province on 8 Apr 2017.

The Sichuan provincial CDC confirmed the positive result of H7N9 in a patient sample on the night of 7 Apr 2017. The patient, a resident in Yunguang village of Gaosheng town in Anyue county, was receiving treatment in Anyue county's Chinese Medicine Hospital. No close contacts showed ILI symptoms so far, and live poultry markets were closed in Anyue county (although no clear live poultry contact history of the patient was reported).

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

******
[4] Gansu
Date: 7 Apr 2017
Source: FIC (Flu Information Centre/Flu in China) Eurosurveillance report [edited]
http://www.flu.org.cn/en/news-19233.html


A human H7N9 AIV case was confirmed in Suzhou district of Jiuquan city in Gansu province on 7 Apr 2017.

The 82-year-old male patient lived in Suzhou district of Jiuquan city. He was admitted to hospital due to fever, cough, and muscular soreness on 3 Apr 2017. The throat swab samples of the patient tested positive for H7N9 by provincial and national CDCs. He was in serious condition and remained in hospital for treatment.

Nine close contacts of the patient have shown no ILI symptoms so far.

--
