******
[7] Henan
Date: 7 Apr 2017
Source: FIC (Flu Information Centre/Flu in China) Eurosurveillance report [edited]
http://www.flu.org.cn/en/news-19224.html


A human H7N9 AIV case was reported in Ye county of Pingdingshan city in Henan province.

The 45-year-old female patient is a resident of Ye county of Pingdingshan city. She had onset of fever on 23 Mar 2017 in Chengzhai village and was transferred to the First Affiliated Hospital of Zhengzhou University (in Zhengzhou) on 27 Mar 2017 after 4 days treatment in The First People's Hospital of Pingdingshan. She was in serious condition and remained in hospital for treatment.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Avian influenza A/H7N9 cases continue to be reported from multiple provinces in China, indicating continuous circulation of the virus in primary sources, i.e. live poultry markets, thereby providing opportunities for animal-to-human transmission, a cause for concern and vigilance in implementation of control measures. - Mod.UBA

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4959020,155.]
